gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Lakers 121, Cavaliers 115
gameRecap.excerpt: The Lakers defeated the Cavaliers, 121-115. Anthony Davis led all scorers with 32 points (23 in the 2nd half), 13 rebounds, and three blocks for the Lakers, while LeBron James added 22 points, six rebounds, and six assists in the victory. Donovan Mitchell tallied 22 points, five rebounds, and six assists for the Cavaliers in the losing effort. The Lakers improve to 10-7 on the season, while the Cavaliers fall to 8-8.
